comments.body:
[~buder] I tried native module on the the latest 5.3.0.v20160523083840 and 5.4.0.v20160530173143 but I was not able to reproduce crash you described. Could you create new ticket for this rather than adding comments on this ticket, to track the issue? It would be very welcome if you include full CLI command and output you executed and hopefully source code when needed.

FYI what I did was to create/build module using following CLI commands.

For 5_3_X: 
{code}
> appc new -n TIMOB23246 --id com.appc.TIMOB23246 --sdk 5.3.0.v20160523083840
> cd TIMOB23246/windows
> ti build -p windows --sdk 5.3.0.v20160523083840 --build-only
{code}

For 5_4_X:
{code}
> appc new -n TIMOB23246X54 --id com.appc.TIMOB23246X54 --sdk 5.4.0.v20160530173143
> cd TIMOB23246X54/windows
> ti build -p windows --sdk 5.4.0.v20160530173143 --build-only
{code}

And then in app.js:

{code}
﻿var TIMOB23246 = require('com.appc.TIMOB23246');
var TIMOB23246X54 = require('com.appc.TIMOB23246X54');

Ti.API.info(typeof TIMOB23246);
Ti.API.info(typeof TIMOB23246X54);
{code}
